Additionally, to determine the incremental value of acquisition we calculate **the cash flows for the combined firm** less what $A$ and $B$ could generate separately, these are called **incremental cash flows**. 

Then, to calculate the **synergy** of a merger we can divide the **incremental cash flows** by the **cost of capital**. This way we will find the absolute amount of synergy created by the acquisition. 

Let´s see this in formula $(2)$:
$$
\begin{equation}
\Delta V = \frac{\Delta CF}{\text{Cost of Capital}}
\end{equation}
$$


Where: 

$\Delta CF$ is the Incremental cash flow from acquisition (after-tax), and;

the **Cost of capital** is the Discount rate for $\Delta CF$.

In this task we have to compare two alternatives to acquisition: 

- Fly-By-Night offers $35$ percent of its stock, and; 

- Fly-By-Night offers $12 million in cash.

Let's analyze them!

## 1. Fly-By-Night offers 35 percent of its stock 

This alternative indicates an acquisition through a stock exchange. In this case, the cost of the acquisition can be determined by the amount of cash needed to pay off Fly-By-Night’s stockholders. This value corresponds to the percentage to be paid $(35\%)$ concerning the value of the merged company, see formula $(4)$:

$$
\begin{equation}
\text{Cost of acquisition} = \% \text{ of stock offered}\times V_{AB}                           	
\end{equation}
$$

Considering $V_{AB}  = V_A +V_B + \Delta V$, then: 


$$
\begin{align*}
\begin{array}{c}
\text{Cost of}\\ 
\text{acquisition}
\end{array}   

&= \% \text{ of stock offered}\times (V_A +V_B + \Delta V)\\[10pt]
&= \% \text{ of stock offered}\times\left(
\begin{array}{c}
\text{Market value}\\ 
\text{of Fly-By-Night}
\end{array}
+
\begin{array}{c}
\text{Value of}\\ 
\text{Flash-in-the-Pan}\\ 
\text{to Fly-By-Night}  
\end{array}   
\right)                    	
\end{align*}
$$

Therefore, let's calculate the cost of acquisition!
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Cost of acquisition} &= 35\% \times (\$13,387,500 +\$21,000,000) \\[10pt]
& = 0.35 \times \$34,387,500  \\[10pt]
&= \$12,035,625
\end{align*}
$$


## 2.	Fly-By-Night offers $12 million in cash. 
This alternative indicates an acquisition through a cash payment. The cost of acquisition is the amount of cash offered: $\$12,000,000$.
